section.def:
party
                (一方當事人), in relation to a petition, means the
            petitioner or the respondent;

petition
                (呈請、呈請書) means
            an election petition;

petitioner
                (呈請人), in relation to a petition, means the
            person who lodges the petition;

Registrar
                (司法常務官) means the Registrar of the High
            Court;

subparagraph.content:
by leaving it at, or sending it by post or by recorded delivery or by a
                        registered letter to, the party’s last known residence in Hong Kong;
                        or
